{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013jKMqXmVHKVzvikssKE3SE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The command exits 0 and prints \"pong\". \n\nHere's what was done:\n\n- **Root cause:** `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")` uses the GCS (cluster-internal) protocol. This requires a local raylet process to be running on the client — without it, Ray looks for a local session file that doesn't exist and times out.\n\n- **Fix:** The updated script calls `ray start --address=ray-head:6379` first to spin up a local raylet that joins the cluster, then `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")` succeeds because the local session exists.\n\n- The ConfigMap `ray-job-script` was patched with the new script, and the `ray-client` pod was recreated (subPath mounts don't hot-reload, so a pod restart was needed)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":197,"cache_read_input_tokens":53961,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":197},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1734c123-7583-4068-93c3-32de6f12ae51","uuid":"5a540e14-6689-4f6e-9914-b116496872e6","request_id":"req_011CcRK3atemqtgbtjF4TFzh"}
